{"lemma":"أَصْفَرَ","slug":"أَصْفَرَ","root":"ص.ف.ر","root_slug":"ص-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ف-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":9,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24455","n24483"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"yellow (“having yellow as its color”)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to empty, to void, to vacate, to evacuate, to free"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of صَفْر (ṣafr), elative degree of صِفْر (ṣifr), elative degree of صُفْر (ṣufr), elative degree of صَفِر (ṣafir), elative degree of صُفُر (ṣufur)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of صَفْر (ṣafr), elative degree of صِفْر (ṣifr), elative degree of صُفْر (ṣufr), elative degree of صَفِر (ṣafir), elative degree of صُفُر (ṣufur):; emptier, more void; emptiest, most void"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ص ف ر (ṣ f r).\n\nElative of صَفْر (ṣafr, “empty, void”) and صِفْر (ṣifr, “(same)”) and صُفْر (ṣufr, “(same)”) and صَفِر (ṣafir, “(same)”) and صُفُر (ṣufur, “(same)”)."},"ipa":["/ʔasˤ.far/","/ʔasˤ.fa.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24455","headword_ar":"اصفرّ","root":"Sfr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It become"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSofar","text_ar":"اَصْفَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yellow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M, K:) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASfAr~","text_ar":"اصفارّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was so constantly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was so transiently."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA. [See 9 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hmr","text_ar":"حمر"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n24483","headword_ar":"اَصْفَرُ","root":"Sfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[a comparative and superlative epithet form"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Safara","text_ar":"صَفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSofaru mino bulobulK","text_ar":"اَصْفَرُ مِنْ بُلْبُلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A greater whistler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"warbler, than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blbl","text_ar":"بلبل"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiforN","text_ar":"صِفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, empty, void,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vacant."},{"kind":"text","text":"] It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSofaru Albuyuwti mina","text_ar":"اَصْفَرُ البُيُوتِ مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxayori Albayotu AlS~iforu mino kitaAbi A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"الخَيْرِ البَيْتُ الصِّفْرُ مِنْ كِتَابِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That one of houses which is the most void of good is the house that is destitute of the Book of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.)       -A3-  Also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Yellow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the colour termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuforapN","text_ar":"صُفْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, K:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaforaA='u","text_ar":"صَفْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, &c.:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuforN","text_ar":"صُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Black"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, S, K) is sometimes thus termed: (S:) applied to a camel, as in the Kur lxxvii. 33, because a black camel always has an intermixture of yellow: (TA:) or, applied to a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a colour whereof the ground is black, with some yellow hairs coming through."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) Applied to a horse,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of the colour termed in Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zarodaho","text_ar":"زَرْدَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of sorrel"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S,) but not unless"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a yellow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorrel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tail and mane."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banuw AlA^aSofari","text_ar":"بَنُو الاَصْفَرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Greeks"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~uwmu","text_ar":"الرُّومُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (S, A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their kings:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the sons of El-Asfar the son of Room the son of 'Eesoo (or 'Eysoon, TA, [i. e. Esau,]) the son of Is-hák [or Isaac] (K) the son of Ibráheem [or Abraham]: (TA:) or El-Asfar was a surname of Room: (TA:) or they were so called because their first ancestor, (A, IAth,) Room the son of 'Eysoon, (IAth,) was of a yellow complexion: (A, IAth:) or because they were conquered by an army of Abyssinians by whom their women had yellow children: (K:) [or] they are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the modern Muscovites."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSofaraAni","text_ar":"الاَصْفَرَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gold and saffron;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;) which are said to destroy women: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the plant called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waros","text_ar":"وَرْس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and saffron:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the plant called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waros","text_ar":"وَرْس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and gold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saffron and raisins."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, Sgh, K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~aforaA='u","text_ar":"الصَّفْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gold."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuforN","text_ar":"صُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) Hence the saying of 'Alee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA","text_ar":"يَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaforaA='u A@Sofar~iY wayaA bayoDaA='u A@boyaD~iY wagur~iY gayoriY","text_ar":"صَفْرَا=ءُ ا@صْفَرِّى وَيَا بَيْضَا=ءُ ا@بْيَضِّى وَغُرِّى غَيْرِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O gold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be yellow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and O silver,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be white, and beguile other than me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lifulaAnK SaforaA='u","text_ar":"مَا لِفُلَانٍ صَفْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA bayoDaA='u","text_ar":"وَلَا بَيْضَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not belonging to such a one gold nor silver"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of bile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well-known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the yellow bile; one of the four humours of the body;"},{"kind":"text","text":"of which the others are the black bile ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~awodaA='u","text_ar":"السَّوْدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), the blood ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~amu","text_ar":"الدَّمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and the phlegm ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albalogamu","text_ar":"البَلْغَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"):] so called because of its colour. (M.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bow that is made of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tree called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naboE","text_ar":"نَبْع"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, * K, * TA.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The female locust that is devoid of eggs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft tracts, and of the sands,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sometimes growing in hard level ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain herb, that spreads upon the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leaves of which are like those of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xas~","text_ar":"خَسّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lettuce"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (AHn, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which the camels eat vehemently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, M:) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwr","text_ar":"ذُكُور"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Aboo-Nasr, M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA","A","IAth","AHn"]}]}}